---

**reclaimed** is a cross-platform, ultra-lightweight, and surprisingly powerful command-line tool for analyzing disk usage ‚Äî with special handling for iCloud storage on macOS.  
Quickly find your largest files and directories with a beautiful, color-coded interface, and manage them through an interactive terminal UI.  
Fully supports **Linux**, **macOS**, and **Windows**.

---

## ‚ú® Features

- üöÄ **Legitimately Performant**: Fast recursive directory scanning with ultra-efficient progress updates.
  - Carefully tuned repaint frequency ‚Äî optimized to avoid slowing results by even 5ms.
  - Separate thread for the clock to keep real-time updates buttery smooth.
- ‚òÅÔ∏è **iCloud Smartness**: Detects and handles iCloud Drive symlink files vs local storage (macOS).
- üìä **Beautiful UI**: Powered by [Textualize/rich](https://github.com/Textualize/rich) and [Textualize/textual](https://github.com/Textualize/textual).
  - Full keyboard navigation, mouse support, and customizable themes.
- üñ•Ô∏è **Interactive Terminal UI**: Browse, manage, and delete files/directories with ease.
- üóëÔ∏è **Safe Deletion**: Remove large files and directories directly from the interface ‚Äî with confirmation prompts.
- üíæ **Export to JSON**: Save scan results for further analysis or batch operations.
- ‚ö° **Real-Time Feedback**: Live progress indicators and graceful handling of permission issues.
- üõ°Ô∏è **Actual Privacy**: 100% offline. No telemetry, no analytics, no tracking - can't even check for updates.

